 awards: April 24, 2020  Annual Graduate College Outstanding Thesis and Dissertation Award    Program/Department nominations due to the Graduate College: October 25, 2019  Announcement of awards: December 2, 2019  Award for Graduate Research  Fall 2019  Applications/Department nominations due to the Graduate College: October 18, 2019  Announcement of awards: December 2, 2019  Spring 2020  Applications/Department nominations due to the Graduate College: March 20, 2020  Announcement of awards: April 20, 2020  Dean’s Scholar Fellowship    Department nominations due to the Graduate College: March 13, 2020  Announcement of awards: April 20, 2020  Last day for awardees to inform Graduate College of acceptance: June 1, 2020  Graduate Mentoring Award  Graduate Mentoring Awards are designed to encourage and award excellence and innovation in all aspects of graduate mentoring. Each year the Graduate College will provide up to four awards of $2,000 each per year.   The 2020 deadline has been extended from March 1 to March 6 (4PM).  Winners will be announced around April 20, 2020   Provost’s Graduate Internship Award   Student submits completed application and related documents to their degree program. Contact your degree program for their deadline and instructions (program will need sufficient time to review and process before their submission date listed below)  Director of Graduate Studies uploads application and related documents via the Graduate College website: March 20, 2020 EXTENDED TO APRIL 1, 2020  Announcement of Awards: April 20, 2020  Provost’s Graduate Research Award   Student submits completed application and related documents to their degree program. Contact your degree program for their deadline and instructions (program will need sufficient time to review and process before their submission date listed below)  Director of Graduate Studies uploads application and related documents via the Graduate College website (under For Faculty/Staff, access restricted): October 14 2019  Announcement of Awards: December 2, 2019.  SROP Early Admissions Fellowship  The candidate formally applies to UIC and their SROP mentor submits a nomination to the graduate program Director of Graduate Studies (DGS) by December 15, 2019.  UIC Pipeline to an Inclusive Faculty (PIF) Program  Nominees for the Access (Recruitment) Fellowship and University Fellowships are automatically considered for the PIF.  University Fellowship   Department nominations due to the Graduate College: February 3, 2020  Announcement of awards: February 26, 2020  Last day for awardees to inform Graduate College of acceptance: April 15, 2020           Funding & Awards    Back to main content           Graduate Funding Overview     April 15th Resolution    Assistantships      Fellowships & Awards     Fellowship Office Information    Graduate College Tuition & Fee Waivers    UIC Pipeline to an Inclusive Faculty (PIF) Program    Graduate College Professional Success Program (PSP) for Fellows    Emergency Grants      Other Funding     Online Funding Resources    National & International Opportunities                     UIC Logo         Graduate  College           Campus Resources    Academic Calendar    UIC Today    Event Calendar    UIC Maps    Visit & Directions    Clery Compliance    Nondiscrimination Policy    Title IX: Sexual Misconduct    Student Information Disclosures      Staff Resources    my UIC    UIC Outlook Online    GoogleApps@UIC    Site Login      Student Resources    Wellness Center    Writing Center    UIC Pop-Up Pantry         Contact   Graduate College  601 S. Morgan St., 604 UH, 192, Chicago, Illinois 60607-7106  Phone: (312) 413-2550  Fax: (312) 413-0185  gradcoll@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    LinkedIn    Twitter    Instagram             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI 